The tested device (DUT) is a BGP route reflector for 6PE (IPv6 over BGP-LU
with IPv4 next hops). It runs OSPFv2 and LDP with a P-router over an IPv4-only
core, and has IPv4 IBGP sessions with PE routers (RR clients) another
PE-router. The hosts are attached via IPv6-only links and communicate using
IPv6 across the MPLS core.

